casts.text: So if you’re a /diet-coke enthusiast, all of your followers will see your silly casts about caffeine in their home feeds, even if they prefer /coffee or Pepsi. But with narrowcasts, you can limit your casts to only followers of /diet-coke.

FAQ

1. What happens when I narrowcast?
> Normally, when you cast in a channel it goes out to all of your followers—regardless of whether they follow the channel. So if you’re a /diet-coke enthusiast, all of your followers will see your silly casts about caffeine in their home feeds, even if they prefer /coffee or Pepsi. But with narrowcasts, you can limit your casts to only followers of /diet-coke.

Note: this is a Warpcast-only behavior for now. Other clients are free adopt or disregard this.

2. Are narrowcasts part of the protocol?
> No. They’re an experiment.

3. How long will you run the experiment?
> For a couple weeks. If it has low usage, we will likely remove. If usage looks good, we’ll work on incorporating into the protocol.

4. I want to see all casts from everyone I follow even if they narrowcast but I don’t want to follow every channel!
> Try using another client like @supercast or @herocast
